-- Countrywide Financial, Acorn reach subprime agreement
-- 
-- Mon Feb 11, 2008 6:25am EST
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2008/02/11/us-countrywide-acorn-idUSWEN387720080211

 

 (Reuters) - Mortgage lender Countrywide Financial Corp and housing advocacy group ACORN said they have reached an agreement to formalize workout programs to help borrowers with all types of subprime loans avoid foreclosure. 

 The agreement addresses home retention options and procedures for borrowers in various stages of mortgage delinquency, the companies said in a statement. (Reporting by Jennifer Robin Raj in Bangalore; Editing by Deepak Kannan)